					<h2> Reading/Writing Memory </h2>
				</header>
					
				<p id="instructions_text">
					Some of the most basic instructions in x86 assembly are reading and writing memory. <br />
					The <span class="mov_instruction">mov</span> instruction writes data from one register into another. <br />
					Moving data between registers is possible, but moving data between memory addresses directly is not. <br />
					The <span class="push_instruction">push</span> and <span class="pop_instruction">pop</span> instructions
					push and pop data from the current stack in memory. <br /> 
					Memory stacks depend on the type of hardware being used. 
				</p>
				
				<br />
				
