				</header>
				
				<p id="math_instructions_text"> 
				Basic math instructions in x86 use two 32-bit registers. <br />
				These instructions include addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, and bit shifting. <br />
				For example, the following instructions would add the generated value in the EAX register to the one in the ECX register. <br />
				</p>
				
				<blockquote id="addl">
				<span id="eaxRandom"><%= eaxResult %></span> <br>
		
